##Hubei female worker: Trapped by epidemic, tied up with housework

Micro-signal Jianjiaobuluo

Function description, pepper tribe, amplify your voice! Chinese Women Workers Exclusive Information Platform, you are welcome to pay attention!

ABSRTACT: "Does it count as a worthwhile thing to care about the family's food and drink? "

This spring, everyone was cooped up at home, eating, sleeping, and swiping their cell phones. But their lives are a little different.
They keep an eye out for masks and disinfectant, worry about the health of their families, and are eager to return to work in Shenzhen, but there is no hope for them, said Three Meals a Day, an assistant professor at the University of Hong Kong.
They are female workers from Hubei.

"The whole place is sealed off with barbed wire. "
Working in Shenzhen for more than a decade, this was Wan Wan's longest Spring Festival in his hometown of Tianmen, Hubei Province.
In Shenzhen, a city where work never stops, there has always been a rush to resume work after the eighth day of the Lunar New Year. Of the eight million migrant workers, a considerable proportion are from Hubei Province. Often come to the Green Rose Social Work Service Center sisters, in the factory, on the site, do catering, as a clerk... Shenzhen's GDP, they are one hand done.
But now: "Our village is sealed off, the entrances and exits are sealed, the streets are sealed off, and everywhere is sealed off with barbed wire, like in a war, " Wan said, "Don't even think about taking a bus. " She had planned to take her nephew's bus to town and then transfer from town to Shenzhen, only to be told that the bus was out of service and that her nephew couldn't take it out either.
Lulu of Xiaogan, Hubei Province, and Le Xuan of Jingzhou, Hubei Province, have not left their homes for more than a month because of the quarantine. These places are the hardest hit areas of the epidemic, empty streets filled with the smell of disinfectant, behind do not know how much life and death staged. Most of the way home will go through Wuhan, and we were still lack of vigilance to the virus, after hearing the news home after panic, until the end of 14 days at home to begin to rest assured. Wan Wan Wan heard that a newly diagnosed case is only a few hundred meters from his home, even more afraid to go out.

The slogan of Wan Wan's hometown
(photos provided by the workers themselves)
In Shenzhen, where they can not return, Yi Yi, from Huanggang, Hubei Province, is spending the new year away for the first time in 20 years, but she is eager for the city to open so she can visit her mother, who lives alone in her hometown.
Between them, is a line of iron and barbed wire made of the checkpoint.

Wondering what to feed my family every day
Village, a small area, buying food and cooking has become a problem, a problem that usually falls on the woman.
"I'm the one who buys the food. I'm the better choice. " Though still in Shenzhen, yi Yi temporarily can not return to do 20 years of Clothing Factory Car Plate Division Post, take care of broken husband, Sick mother-in-law, unable to return to school son, plus responsible for the whole family's Three Meals a Day, became Yi Yi's work.
Her husband usually buys food and cooks together, but he broke a bone accidentally years ago. Her mother-in-law is old and has had surgery, so his resistance is poor. Her son, who is in college, is strong and healthy, but he doesn't know vegetables at all, he prefers to brush his mobile phone and surf the Internet at home rather than go to the market. If a family wants to eat and drink, who will go out if they don't? Although you can buy food online, but fish ah meat, or choose their own more at ease.
The price of pork has gone up so much that people are afraid to buy it. Usually 28,29 yuan a catty, the new year that two days fly up to more than 50 also just, now 38,39 a catty is the normal. "How expensive! " Yi sighed, "So we all eat very little meat and often vegetables, but think about it, the old man is not well, the husband is sick, and the children need nutrition, so we still need to buy some meat. We'll just get some meat for the soup, and we'll cook some noodles with the soup. It was the same at dinner on New Year's Day
Lu, who returned to Xiaogan, wasn't worried about vegetables, because her parents had grown a lot of vegetables and had stocked up on New Year's items years ago, so the ingredients were still adequate. But as the days passed, she also began to worry about supplies, counting how much food she had left. Children in the fourth grade are in need of nourishment, but milk and eggs are becoming increasingly extravagant.
Wan Wan Wan is the same. Although the stock of New Year goods, but still intend to save to eat, "water flow" , because do not know when the blockade ends.
The good news is that housework is also fun for these industrious and optimistic women. Yiyi home cooking rice cake, Wan Wan Wan change pattern to do cabbage stew, radish stew, radish stew fish, Lulu also change pattern to do radish, and then make a beautiful shape.

Wan Wan's breakfast for his family
Fruit, steamed bread slices and Porridge

Lulu's homemade carrot sticks

"I do a lot of housework. It's not work. "
Le Xuan was the only sister she met this time who did not cook and was not afraid to say so.
"My brother cooks for us, " said Le Xuan in a brisk voice over the microphone, "My brother is still a good cook. My mother said my brother has to be able to cook and can't always let his wife do it in the future. It's not like in our family where my father does nothing every day and then lets my mother Cook. "
But when it comes to housework, "My brother does the dishes, but he does the cooking; I sweep the floor, mop the floor, clean the table and tidy up the house. My father says, 'my daughter is so lazy, she doesn't do anything. ' "
In her father, the head of the family, cooking is not a man should do, do is a serious "work. ". What about women? Washing the dishes, mopping the floor, doing the laundry, raising the children, are all women's duties, things that are done at random.

Residents can not go out to buy vegetables, supplies unified by the grid agent purchase
(photo courtesy of Le Xuan)
However, there is no shortage of things to do. Four Generations under One Roof, although many people, but she did not want to parents too tired, their own initiative to do more things. Yiyi rental house was and husband two people live, now mother-in-law, son are coming, live, had to go to the factory dormitory, every morning to do health, cooking, evening back to the dormitory. Ten thousand from time to time to steamed rice cake and steamed bread to the family to eat, but also adhere to the daily use of sterile water upstairs and downstairs are dragged again.
This is their share of family responsibilities, the care of the elderly, the health of their family concerns. It's not something you do on the fly.

"Is it a worthy thing to care about the family's food and drink? "
Household and care work, which is often neglected and unrecognized, is becoming more and more prevalent in the epidemic.
Every morning, Lulu would remind her to punch in, prepare for online classes, supervise two online classes in the morning and afternoon, and work with her on homework such as handcrafting and sign language dancing. She often can not get a phone to reply to messages, nor as usual, every day on time to work, weekly cleaning, now every day to do housework, "feel a bit idle time. ".
Since I heard that another community has been diagnosed, the village has issued a disinfectant powder, universal disinfection powder with water to mop the floor, is dragged every day! Husband work, daughter online classes, million on the contract than Shenzhen rental housing several times the health of the house.

Wan Wan Wan gets up every morning to disinfect the floor
Yiyi pay attention to the purchase of masks and disinfectant information, but also do not dare to let the old children out, in order to buy food to bite the bullet to go out. Since she can't work, she sits at home for a while and wants to do some housework. Her mother-in-law always has to do the dishes. They feel "uncomfortable if they don't move, " but her son and husband can always play on their cell phones, sitting and lying down for a while.
Yiyi said: "How do not feel to do so much work, but also tired than work? IS TIRED! To worry about too many things, but a free down, and want to find something meaningful to do. "
I asked, "is it a worthwhile thing for you to be in charge of your family's food and drink? "
She laughed at the remark, and it made sense. "compared to those who are sick, we are doing very well. After all, the whole family can still be noisy together and take care of their health. "
The huge amount of housework and caring that women do requires our own recognition and praise.

"I want to go back. "
Everyone is eager to return to Shenzhen to start work, because housework is not valued as a result of home chores do not get money.
"What can I say at home? It's a little easier, but it's not very comfortable, and it's mainly because there's no financial source. " Wan Wan is thinking like this. In Shenzhen, although it's hard work, and even though a few square meters of rental housing is not spacious, but after cutting out 600 yuan in rent, water and electricity, aFTER $300 in living expenses, that leaves two thousand a month. How about now? Because the old can only work part-time, do not work means no income. "I don't spend much money at home either. The problem is that I have to keep paying the rent in Shenzhen. I don't have much money. I hope I can make money earlier... I really want to go back. "

The rent from the yiks'place
A 12-square-foot room for 800
In Shenzhen, Yi Yi can feel the vigilance of Hubei People. Her son went to college in Jiangxi, and after the outbreak, the school set up a group for all Hubei Students, saying that the return of Hubei people to school would be notified separately, and that it didn't feel good to be treated differently. According to the factory where several people have returned to work: "did not inform me, do not know because I am Hubei People. The specific who went to work is not clear. "
Asked if there were similar concerns in Lulu, "It's impossible to estimate when you'll be able to go out, " she wrote before her children's 7 a.m. online class. "The city will have to open its doors. We won't make trouble for society. We'll go out when we're told to. Hubei people don't equal a virus. "
